Product: Wireless Earbuds, yobola Bluetoth Earbuds, IPX5 Waterproof Wireless Headphones Touch Control, Bluetoth Headphones 5.1 Built-in Microphone, 25 Hrs with USB-C Charging with Running/Fitness
Text: I am a real fan of headphones, probably because I'm somewhat older and that is what I grew up using. I don't often use earbuds but I do have a couple pair to use when travelling or outside. One of the problems I have using earbuds is the wire always seems to get in the way. This isn't an issue with my headphones because I only use those chilling in the house, but when doing yard work and the like, I do enjoy having music. My nephew let me try his airpods and they were an obvious and amazing solution except for the price. No way I could ever justify that for my use.When I saw this pair online I was somewhat skeptical but for the price I thought these might be the answer to my problem. Honestly, they work so well that I am floored. The tap to answer a phone call thing is really cool. The people on the other end of the phone call can hear me just fine so the microphone works well. The sound quality is very good and better than I would have been satisfied to enjoy from a product so well priced, that was the biggest surprise. The batteries work exactly as advertised and I think it is cool that the charged case can charge the buds so many times. The only critique I have is earbuds I used in the past have always been the kind with the gel pieces on the end. For me these are not quite as comfortable as that type but I know this is the style. If they came out with one that had a softer end, I would spend more money and buy that one also. No reason at all not to hit the buy now button on this.
Label: Suspicious

Product: Wireless Earbuds, yobola Bluetoth Earbuds, IPX5 Waterproof Wireless Headphones Touch Control, Bluetoth Headphones 5.1 Built-in Microphone, 25 Hrs with USB-C Charging with Running/Fitness
Text: To be honest.  I wasn't expecting much when I purchased them. There was a coupon that discounted these 30% and were under $20 so why not give them a try.I was pleasantly surprised how easy they connected to my phone. They headset buttons are multifunctional which is great such has volume up/down, pause/play and skip tracks.  It does take a little time to get use to it due to the time you press and/or how long you hold the button down for.Battery life is pretty long and the case is a self charging case. I haven't plugged it in for a charge for over a week and they work great with no issues. I have only used these for music and the quality is really good especially for the price. You can't compare these with higher quality music headphones because there's a huge price difference however I'm very please with the sound quality.Now comparing the quality and price to the other fruit brand? Personally I don't feel its worth paying $100+ more for those. Yes quality might be better but $100 worth better? No.  I work for a top Fortune 15 company in technology and these are worth it.Only dislikes would be that the charging case seems flimsy and the ear buds don't fit perfectly in my ear. You need to move then around at times for the best fit yet they are pretty light and comfortable. I do prefer earbuds with gel inserts which these don't have. They do however have the same fitment as the famous fruit brand ear buds. So if those fit you well then these are the same. Im just not a fan of the shape. Also at times if you move them around for a better fit, you accidently might press the button which stops or pauses the music you're playing, no big deal though.All in all a fantastic wireless bluetooth headset for the low price.
Label: Not Suspicious

Another key element is they are more comfortable than my airbuds that's really important too if you're goung to wear them for a long time  I use them for driving sometimes well with one Bud and for music in my house with both in,  which helps me to get things done!:) Overall a great product I would buy again for sure!

Product: Wireless Earbuds, yobola Bluetoth Earbuds, IPX5 Waterproof Wireless Headphones Touch Control, Bluetoth Headphones 5.1 Built-in Microphone, 25 Hrs with USB-C Charging with Running/Fitness
Text: So I never write reviews online, but feel compelled to do so for this purchase because of how blown away I am by these earbuds.I can't find my t14's for the life of me and, upon the pre-gym self-loathing in my truck today (lol) at the thought of a workout without them, I began browsing Amazon for the same pair.Sadly, I couldn't find them, but I am happy to have happened upon these!Not only did they show up in less than 6 hours from the moment I ordered them in the gym parking lot (seriously Amazon, this is getting a bit scary haha!), but I just tested them out and am blown away at the sound quality I received for only having spent $25 (plus tax it came out to around 27)! They paired in under a minute as well.I'm deaf in my left ear, so wearing both buds can be superfluous, but these actually give off enough bass to give me the sensation of "hearing" on my deaf side. For those who dont understand, because I only went deaf in that ear 2 years ago, it helps u feel less "imbalanced", so it's a HUGE plus for me with my vertigo. You can still tell there's some sort of sound happening.The only downside I can see is that, when I went to test them, they seemed a bit larger than my old ones. However, I haven't worn my old ones in a very long time, as I've been going to the gym with a friend and enjoying her company instead, so I'm hoping my ears just have to adapt to them.Overall, I'm very pleased with my purchase and hope you are too if you order these! :)Ps- the packaging they came in was also very nice. They're encased in the black foam you'd typically see in gun cases, or cases for musical instruments and such, not some cheap plastic. Not sure if this matters, but it makes me feel like the company is just putting a little extra thought into their customer's experience!
Label: Suspicious

Text: Lost my AirPods, needed a quick pair of wireless earbuds to tie me over until I replaced the AirPods.Now Let’s be clear, for the price paid ~~~$25.49 - 30% = $17.84~~~ the sound quality is astronomically outstanding. I was expecting crap sounding wireless Bluetooth earbuds with a semi ok mic, what I got was decent sounding earpiece and ok mic. I can take calls, listen to YouTube videos and playback music. Each sounds okay at best and for my quick needs, it’s a solution.These were design with a specific individual in-mind and it works. Now this only takes until account the sound quality and not the design as they feel STUPIDLY CHEAP and flimsy. But beggars can’t be choosers.Now these are NOT AirPods killers or replacements, but are a convenient quick fix simple solution to a pair of wireless earbuds for taking calls and video playback and that’s exactly what I was looking for.They’re cheap, affordable and decent. Would I buy again? Sure for the same price. If the price is higher than $20 then No I wouldn’t as other brand make better quality products (like SkullCandy, JBL, and Anker) for $10-$20 more.These are a bargain price, bargain sound pair of Bluetooth wireless earbuds that are convenient and decent, nothing more and nothing less. They check off the needs and delivers on the quality per price tag. 7/10.

Text: Yes, my AirPods broke. My first instinct was to grab another box with Apple product but Amazon played a decent trick on me - they displayed other headphones that "look like" AirPods but cost small fraction of what Apple is asking. Is there any catch? Well, after reading reviews of YOBOLA wireless headphones I was convinced that it is more than worth to give them a try especially that price was so much more palatable than Apple's AirPods. There is not much point writing long review about headphones so I will be brief. After comparing AirPods (2nd generation) to Yobola, the latter one is a clear winner. Why?1. Sounds quality - Yobola sounds better especially in the lower range - i.e. much better bass2. Features - Yobola lets you adjust volume just by touch - something that Airpods cannot do. Other than that both Apple and Yobola are quite similar. BTW integration with an iPhone is flawless with both pairs of headphones3. Price -  you can get 5 Yobola headphones for the price of one Apple productIn summary I am giving YOBOLA 5 stars. Definitely worth a try

Text: I purchased these as a backup for my airpods. I wanted something I could carry around the city and not fear the financial pain of losing one of the ear buds. These are well priced ($20 -  not worth more than that). The sound quality for music is perfectly fine - to the people complaining about the sound quality - go buy the $150 - $250 Apple Airpods or Samsung pods, and chill, these are not meant to replace those.Sound quality for music: 7/10 (a lot of bass, and sounds very full; somewhat cancels noise)Sound quality for talk: 8/10 (excellent quality - my 64 year old mom could hear me perfectly and I could hear her quite well also)Range: Decent, as people have been saying, you can walk several feet away and quality will be fine.CONSI expect the battery life to be sub par (for long trips I would bring along my airpods). I'm sure these won't last anywhere near 12 or 24 hours.THESE DO NOT PAIR WITH MACBOOK PRO M1 LAPTOPS.For me, this was the biggest letdown. Apple has a new line of computers that fall under the M1 chip. Unfortunately, these earbuds do not pair with the new laptops. So just be aware that if you have a Macbook you may not be able to use these buds with your laptop.I DO recommend purchasing these as a backup pair of earbuds, but I would not purchase these again knowing that they are not compatible with the M1 Macbook Pro line.

Text: These earbuds are an excellent value.  They have about 90% of the features of Airpods at an unbelievable price.  I was pleasantly surprised with how nice the build quality was, given how inexpensive these are.  The design is nice and sleek.I bought these to replace my broken Airpods and I've noticed only a couple of minor differences that aren't an issue for me personally:1.  The case does not pair to your phone so you cannot tell exactly how much battery life is left in your case.  The case has an indicator light that flashes when it is below 10% and needs charging.2.  You need to accept phone calls from your earbuds in order for the call to be taken on your earbuds.  If you answer a call on your phone screen, the call will be taken on your phone as well.3.  There are no sensors on the earbuds that automatically start/stop music when your remove/put in the earbuds from your ears.  You need to start/stop manually using the earbud tap functions (I prefer this personally)4.  The tap functions are not programmable like with the Airpods, but all the basic functions you'd expect and need are already there.Overall, these are excellent earbuds for the price.  They're such great value that I bought multiple so I could have one in my office, car, and home.
Label: Suspicious

Text: Initially I absolutely loved these ear buds.  They fit well and stayed in throughout a variety of activities.  The touch sensor was the only initial complaint as it didn't seem to always respond on a first touch.  However, I've only had this product for a few months and the volume capability of the ear buds began to fade.  It started with the left ear bud being a lot quieter than the other and as I liked to have the option to run one ear bud at a time if desired but even on the highest volume setting and trying all potential software settings, it is barely audible with any type of ambient noise.  Than 2 weeks ago the right ear bud had the same issue.  I have volume turned all the way up and these ear buds just no longer perform.  Something has clearly gone wrong with them and rendered them useless.  I tried to use them on a plane ride the other day and I couldn't hear anything over the ambient noise of the plan in flight.  The product is just not built for the long haul which is disappointing as it had such a promising start at the beginning.

Text: I've been a holdout on wireless earbuds for a while now, but I wanted to be able to move around the house while listening to audiobooks on my phone. I had previously bought a different pair for about twice the price but didn't like them because they were bulky and wouldn't stay in my ears. I decided to give these a shot based on the positive reviews and the low price. After using them for a few weeks, I'm really happy with them and so far am glad I didn't spend way more. They fit in my ears pretty well (one side doesn't fit quite as well as the other, but it does stay in for the most part...not sure I'd be comfortable running or doing other intense activities with these in, though). The battery life seems awesome, as I will sometimes listen to these for several hours a day and don't charge the case more than maybe once a week, and I have yet to run the battery down to the point where they're unusable. I don't do the best with all of the various types of taps that perform different functions, but I can pause and play and adjust the volume without any trouble, so these are user-friendly in that regard.

Text: Was dubious about getting wireless headphones because so many people had told me they always break/people can never hear them on the phone/expensive so I thought I’d test it out with a pair of fairly cheap ones.They look similar to the apple air pods, they’re light, don’t really feel them in my ears once in.People can hear me fine on the phone and the battery life is really good. I use them everyday for at least an hour and I haven’t charged the case yet (bought them early June 2022).The sound quality isn’t great, not a huge amount of bass but the mids/treble are very clear. However they’re fine to use for your commute, casual music/podcast listening etc. The volume is fine, not quiet which I thought they might be. I wouldn’t say they’re noise cancelling but I wasn’t expecting them to be as they’re not over the ear cans with padding to isolate the noise.They are small and light so I’ve flung one across the room by accident when taking a jumper off because I forgot I had them in so I can imagine they’re easy to lose (but that’s not a fault of the manufacturer) however I have constant porridge brain and I’ve not lost them yet!!They pair to your phone/ipad/laptop as soon as you take them out of the charger pouch (post setup) and doesn’t call for a mad set up time.Overall VERY happy with my earphones, would definitely recommend to anyone wanting to dip their toe in the wireless headphone pool!

Text: Last year I initially bought the T2 model, which worked perfectly. This year I decided to update to the T9 model. In the beginning when I put them on there was a very noticeable difference between the sound quality of the two, the bass is better, the sound goes higher, the noise cancelation is better, at first look it is overall a bettered product. I loved them so much I got a second pair for a friend's birthday. And then all of a sudden my left ear bud stopped working. While I am becoming deaf with my right ear bud, the left one seems to be not even on. I can only hear it in a silent room and if the volume is at its highest. Even then I am struggling to hear properly from it, it seems like the front part of the speakers of the ear bud have completely shut out and only the back ones are working. The noise is so faint, that you can't even decipher what words are being said, you can just hear some very very quiet noise. I would have expected them to work at least for a year like the T2 version (which still works perfectly fine and is currently being used by my grandma) but instead it didn't even last 3 months, so disappointing. Even more disappointing because I've already gotten my friend a pair as well and they would probably stop working in no time too. Do not recommend getting them especially for that price.

Product: Wireless Earbuds, yobola Bluetoth Earbuds, IPX5 Waterproof Wireless Headphones Touch Control, Bluetoth Headphones 5.1 Built-in Microphone, 25 Hrs with USB-C Charging with Running/Fitness
Text: These babies have been a total dream! I am a total podhead (listen to a lot of podcasts) so I bought these as a low commitment practice run for AirPods to see if I’d lose or forget to charge them… #adhdproblems. I definitely expected them to be a bit crap at £20 but they have surpassed all expectations - I’m not even going to bother getting the Apple version. Battery life is great, they last about a week and I use them every day. They connect to my phone easily and automatically as soon as I take them out of the case - I’ve also connected to my laptop without any issues. The touch command is pretty good - contrastingly much better than my boyfriend’s £300 Samsung earbuds which he has to dramatically smack himself round the head to pause. I have frustratingly small ear holes but they fit well, maybe slightly less comfortably than their Apple counterparts, but not everyone has ridiculously tiny ears. Haven’t lost them yet but, if I do, I’ll just buy more! Super cheap, super cheerful!
Label: Suspicious

Text: These work a treat. They connected straight away and just worked. I'm not an audiophile but, to my untrained ear, the sound quality was excellent and plenty loud enough. Text: Manufacturerers of sound equipment should know that the prime reason people buy their products is foremost their sound quality. Here you have a product that is the aural equivalent of listening to a bee in a tincan. There is no bass, no oomph, no sound quality. I have no doubt that voice call reception is clear and clean but I didn't buy ear buds to make phone calls. I have other gadgets for that. I don't care about all the other features these buds may have because they are the worst way to listen to music since those horrible little transistor radios in the 1960's.Absolutely awful. So bad that I'm shocked Amazon sell them let alone endorse them. If these earbuds fell out of a Christmas cracker I would be disappointed.To give you one example: listening to Bob Marley sing One Love through these earbuds makes him sound 14 years old because all the baritone mellow timbre of his mature voice is lost.
Label: Suspicious
